title: HDL cholesterol is carried by apoA particles, which can cross the endothelium in both directions easily. LDL is carried by apoB, which tends to get stuck in the arterial wall. That's bad, because they get oxidized there, which makes them toxic. This causes atherosclerosis. The oxidation causes them to clump together and stick around.
pid: 6f73bce0-898e-4fd6-84bb-b7b97994abbf
